{% layout "layout.liquid" %}
{% block content %}
<div class="flex flex-col items-center">
    <div class="card bg-base-200 w-full mx-8 md:mx-0 md:w-2/3 p-4 shadow-xl">
        <div class="prose">
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <h2>What data is collected?</h2>
            <p>When you use this website, we collect the following data:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Your Mastodon username</li>
                <li>Your Mastodon access token</li>
                <li>Details about the instance you are logged in to</li>
                <li>Your Bluesky handle</li>
                <li>Your Bluesky app password</li>
                <li>An Atproto (the protocol used by Bluesky) session object containing: refreshJwt, accessJwt, handle, did, email, emailConfirmedStatus and emailAuthFactorStatus</li>
                <li>The last time you submitted a toot</li>
                <li>A relation between between your Mastodon and Bluesky post IDs (this is used to enable thread support)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                If you are logged in, you can download a copy of this data by clicking <a
                    href="/account/downloadData">here</a>.
            </p>
            <h2>
                How is this data used?
            </h2>
            <p>
                This data is used to get your latest toots from your Mastodon account, and repost them to Bluesky on a
                scheduled basis.
            </p>
            <h2>
                How is this data stored?
            </h2>
            <p>
                This data is stored in a database on a vServer hosted by <a href="https://www.hetzner.com/">Hetzner</a>
                in NÃ¼rnberg, Germany.
            </p>
            <h2>
                Do we use cookies?
            </h2>
            <p>
                Yes. A http-Cookie is used to store your session. This cookie is deleted when you log out.
            </p>
            <h2>
                Do we disclose any information to outside parties?
            </h2>
            <p>
                No.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}